07/12/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A top Romanian anti-communist dissident died on Friday (December 5th), Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu announced. 
Ticu Dimitrescu, 80, died in his home after hospital treatment for liver disease. 
Dimitrescu won election to parliament in 1989 after the fall of the communist regime and helped draft legislation that resulted in the publication of the Securitate police files. 
He retired from the Senate in 2000. 
Between 1949 and 1964 he spent his life in communist jails or under house arrest for opposing the regime. 
(Agerpress, AP - 05/12/08)
